Deverus 2024-11-17 08:58 p.m.
1.
To start, I am a bar certified attorney holding employment as a prosecutor in the Mayflower Department of Justice. Furthermore, I am a Deputy with the Clark County Sheriff's Office. Both of the aforementioned positions hold high standards of conduct- both in the realm of the law and ethics, and violating such would see all gainful employment which I presently hold revoked.

2.
...While I contest that my actions have done harm to the community, I presently serve as Chief State Attorney for the Public Integrity Division and have conducted prosecutions against police officers and public officials who, in their official capacity and otherwise, have engaged in some form of criminal misconduct, harming the residents of our state and the image and trust with law enforcement. Furthermore, in my employment with the Clark County Sherriff's Office I work on a daily basis to protect the residents of our community from various forms of criminals. In summary; the work I've since undertaken has held public officials, police officers and average criminals accountable for their actions and have protected the community in doing so.

3.
I expect to see myself continuing to be gainfully employed in my current capacity with both the CCSO and DOJ, continuing the work I've started and improving lives as a whole. I'm not a man of large aspirations, nor do I intend to seek any grandeur or political office that would see me going above and beyond what I already do. I simply wish to continue my work and continue to do well for the community, granted with this pesky little trespassing citation knocked off.
